{"key":"post-9472052","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9472052</id>\n<content>As RK said, if you're growing cubes, consider a 1&quot; casing layer MAXimum.&amp;nbsp; However, if you're using a bulk substrate, I see little to no benefit in even using a casing layer.&amp;nbsp; Bulk substrates fruit as well or sometimes better without a casing layer at all, and you get your fruits a week sooner.&amp;nbsp; In the old days, a casing layer helped to make up for sloppy humidity control.&amp;nbsp; If you'll keep watch of your humidity and keep it in the upper 90's, just skip the darned casing.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9472054</next>\n<prev>9472035</prev>\n<first>9471940</first>\n<last>9472069</last>\n<when>1229880746</when>\n<utime>12/21/08 07:32 PM</utime>\n</post>"}